dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.network.ExcludedPortsDetail
dataStructure.description:
The attribute exclusionFunction is designed to be populated from an external management system, and represents the criteria for excluding one or more ResourcePorts. Note that a predefined exclusion function is to limit the role that a ResourcePort plays to an edge role. However, this class enables additional functions to be used to exclude ResourcePorts.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: ExcludedPortsDetail

child.name: excludedRoleList
child.description:
This attribute is a Collection of ResourceRole names. Any ResourceRole name that appears in this Collection MUST be excluded from being part of the Link identified in the resourcePortsInLink aggregation that the instance of this class pertains to.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: excludedRoleList
